This restaurant is in DIRE need of a health inspection. I will never return to Angelica’s after today, unless they make some major adjustments to their service. First, the table we were seated at was filthy, and we had to ask if a host could clean it. The host then proceeded to clean the table with a small napkin that fell apart and barely removed the crumbs from the table. After eating our food, we noticed a pile of garbage on the floor in the kitchen area and a jelly packet on the floor (both pictured in the attached photo.) I don’t know about you, but seeing a pile of garbage in the area where my food is being prepared immediately makes me lose my appetite. It took 20 minutes for an employee to notice the jelly packet and our immediate thought was: what if a customer slipped and injured themselves? The employee who cleaned the jelly off the floor barely picked it up with a small napkin, and had his other hand on the floor. Did I mention that this was the same employee who gave us our eating utensils? Wait, but this isn’t the worst part...  After asking the waitress to remove a charge from our bill for a food item we never received, we walked over to the cash register where we saw a squirming cockroach on the counter. When I told the cashier that there was a bug on the counter, he responded by flicking it behind him where there were containers of ingredients...luckily, it landed on the floor, not on the food. We told the manager that we just noticed a bug, which made us very uncomfortable, and we also noticed the pile of garbage, which just shouldn’t exist in a restaurant. The manager responded by saying, “We had an exterminator come a few months ago, and “we are very busy,” as in too busy to make cleanliness a priority in a restaurant. If you ask me, that’s unheard of since customers are consuming the literal garbage you are charging them for.
...requires a health inspection asap. If you want dirty food, dirty tables, dishes and utensils, you'll love it here.

We get take out all the time, and the food itself is quite delicious, but in person their service leaves a lot to be desired. We'd made a reservation for 8 people for noon, and walk in at 12:05 to see all their tables occupied and only booths open. We had to wait outside for 10 minutes. Then I had to ask for a high chair three times over the course of 15 minutes, until I finally went and got it myself. Then, for some reason, our water orders threw them for a loop. Some people wanted ice, some didn't, and we also wanted a cup with a lid and a straw. The waitress seemed to understand, but did not accurately convey that information to the bus boy who brought us all random waters, only one of which had ice. Food came out promptly and was very tasty, but getting us to that point wasn't super fun.
